## Your Path to Joining Our Team {.unnumbered}

::: {.callout-tip}
## 7-Step Application Process

Follow these steps to join our specialized dental care team:

1. **Create SmallTalk2Me Account** — Set up your account and get ready to showcase your communication skills
2. **Complete IELTS Speaking Assessment (Level 8.5+)** — Demonstrate native-level English proficiency through our structured speaking test
3. **Gather Your Application Materials** — Prepare your resume, references, and work schedule preferences
4. **Submit Your Application Package** — Send everything to our Recruitment Coordinator for review
5. **Complete Position-Specific Knowledge Assessment** — Show your expertise in your chosen role (multiple attempts available)
6. **Schedule Your Interview** — Book your session after passing the previous steps — you're 70% of the way there!
7. **Attend Final Hands-On Evaluation** — Experience our practice firsthand and showcase your clinical skills — nearly there!

After completing all 7 steps, you'll be part of our exclusive pediatric dental care team!
:::

::: {.callout-note}
## Our Commitment to Your Success: Location & Long-Term Career Growth

We prioritize candidates who live near our New Westminster clinic and plan to build a lasting career with our practice. This partnership ensures:

- **Your financial stability** — Minimal commuting costs preserve more of your earnings, especially important for our part-time variable hour roles
- **Your work-life balance** — A short commute means more personal time and reduced daily stress
- **Mutual training investment** — We invest significantly in your specialized development and mentorship
- **10-year career growth** — Long-term commitment unlocks advancement opportunities within our practice

**If your commute to New Westminster exceeds 30 minutes or you plan to relocate**, we still welcome your application! Simply include a brief explanation in your application package (Step 4) about your genuine long-term commitment to remaining with our practice for 10+ years and why this role aligns with your decade-long career vision despite the distance.
:::

