## Step 1: Create SmallTalk2Me Account {#step-1}

::: {.callout-tip}
## Getting Started with Your Assessment

1. Visit [SmallTalk2Me](https://app.smalltalk2.me/){target="_blank"} and create a new account with your email address
2. Verify your email and log in
3. You're now ready for Step 2!

**Progress:** ✓ Step 1 Complete — You've taken the first step toward joining our team!
:::

## Step 2: Complete IELTS Speaking Assessment (Level 8.5+) {#step-2}

::: {.callout-info}
## How to Complete Your Speaking Assessment

1. After logging in to SmallTalk2Me, look for the **[IELTS Speaking Level Test](https://app.smalltalk2.me/ielts)** option
2. Complete the speaking test - you will be asked to:

   - Speak into your microphone.
   - Respond to prompts & answer questions verbally with:
      - Clear and proper intonation with a North American accent.
      - A friendly and cheerful tone of voice (**Watch examples of different tones of voice demonstrated by a pronunciation coach:** [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hPQyHXc1ksA](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hPQyHXc1ksA){target="_blank"}).
   
   ::: {.callout-warning title="Important Instruction"}
   **Please ensure that during the 2-minute speaking task in the middle of the IELTS Speaking Level Test, instead of describing the assigned topic (such as a childhood toy), use this time to thoroughly respond to the following three questions:**

   - **Your short-term and long-term personal and professional goals.**
   - **Why you believe you are a strong candidate for this position.**
   - **Any other information that will help us understand your motivations and aspirations to apply for this position.**

   **How to handle the 2-minute task:**
   - Prepare ahead of time how to use the 2 minutes to answer the self-introduction and these three questions
   - During the 2-minute speaking period, provide a comprehensive self-introduction and thoroughly address all three questions
   - Ignore the templated IELTS mock Speaking Test task card assigned by SmallTalk2Me

   *Our team values honesty and transparency and encourages all applicants to share their experiences fully. Please do not gloss over any information, especially the negative aspects, as we may conduct additional reference checks on your past employment history.*
   :::

3. You will receive an IELTS Speaking Level score (from 0 to 9) for your speaking ability
4. Share your speaking assessment result link with our Recruitment Coordinator

**Progress:** ✓ Step 2 Complete — Congratulations! You've demonstrated native-level communication skills. You're now qualified to proceed to Step 3!
:::

## Excellence Standards for Our Exclusive Team
- **Level 8.5** in *IELTS Speaking* - demonstrating native-level communication skills essential for pediatric care
- Clear North American accent and proper intonation - ensuring optimal patient and family connections
- Approachable, child-friendly communication style - reflecting our specialized focus on ages 0-18

::: {.callout-warning}
## Important Note About Assessment Report
REMEMBER to share the URL link to your complete assessment report that includes:

- All speaking matrices and detailed scores
- Full performance breakdown across all metrics
- Complete evaluation data

DO NOT SHARE the certificate or final score - we need the URL link to review your detailed speaking performance across all evaluation matrices.

**Correct Report Link Format:**  
You can copy the link from the browser address bar when you're on the assessment report page. Your shared link should look like this:  
`https://app.smalltalk2.me/reports/m8v5x3k9qqt4rwwxnb21`, where the `m8v5x3k9qqt4rwwxnb21` part is a unique report ID string. You can copy the link from the browser address bar when you're on the assessment report page.

:::

::: {.callout-note}
## Note
Don't feel discouraged if you cannot pass the first time. We encourage you to work on improving your speaking skills and reapplying in the future if the position is still open. Wishing you the best of luck!
:::

## Step 3: Gather Your Application Materials {#step-3}

::: {.callout-note}
## What You'll Need to Prepare

Before you can submit your application, gather the following materials:

1. **Your Resume** — Highlighting your relevant experience and qualifications
2. **At Least 2 Professional References** — Contact information for people who can speak to your work experience
3. **Your Preferred Work Schedule** — Let us know your availability (2-3 days per week options available)
4. **Your IELTS Assessment Report Link** — Make sure you have the URL link saved from Step 2

**Progress:** ✓ Step 3 Complete — You're now 40% of the way through the application process!
:::

## Step 4: Submit Your Application Package {#step-4}

::: {.callout-tip}
## Your Complete Application Package

Email everything below to **dmd0876@gmail.com** with the position title in the subject line:

1. Your resume
2. Contact information for at least 2 professional references
3. Your SmallTalk2Me [IELTS Speaking Level Test](https://app.smalltalk2.me/ielts) assessment report link (**Level 8.5+** in *IELTS Speaking*)
4. Your preferred work schedule and any scheduling constraints
5. Position title in email subject
6. **Location & Commitment Statement** (if applicable) — If your one-way commute to New Westminster exceeds 30 minutes or you plan to relocate, include a brief paragraph about your long-term commitment to our practice and why you're confident remaining with us for 10+ years despite the distance

**Progress:** ✓ Step 4 Complete — Your application has been submitted! You're 50% through the process. Our team will review your materials and contact your references.
:::

## Step 5: Complete Position-Specific Knowledge Assessment {#step-5}

::: {.callout-important}
## Show Your Expertise

After we review your application and references, you'll complete a position-specific knowledge assessment. Choose your position to view the required assessments:

- [Certified Dental Assistant Knowledge Assessment](certified_dental_assistant.qmd#knowledge-assessment)
- [Procedural Sedation Nurse Knowledge Assessment](procedural_sedation_nurse.qmd#knowledge-assessment)
- [Treatment Coordinator Knowledge Assessment](treatment_coordinator.qmd#knowledge-assessment)
:::

::: {.callout-tip}
## Knowledge Excellence Initiative

- **Open-Book Format** — Demonstrate mastery at your own pace
- **Multiple Attempts** — We support your success with unlimited attempts
- **Comprehensive Coverage** — Show the knowledge that makes our practice exceptional
- **Your Pathway** — Passing this assessment unlocks [Step 6](#step-6) and brings you 70% of the way to joining our team!

**Progress:** ✓ Step 5 Complete — You've demonstrated the specialized knowledge essential for our practice. You're now ready for your interview!
:::

## Understanding Our Practice {.unnumbered}

### Work Environment {.unnumbered}

::: {.callout-note}
## Schedule Details

- **Current Schedule**: 1-2 days per week at Vancouver clinic and 1-2 days per week at New Westminster clinic
- **Flexibility**: Various scheduling options to accommodate work-life balance
:::

### Clinic Locations

- **Vancouver**: 1233 West Broadway
- **New Westminster**: 459 East Columbia Street

::: {.callout-tip}
## Why Local Commitment Matters

Our specialized pediatric care program requires significant training investment in each team member. We're seeking professionals who view this as a long-term home for their career, not a stepping stone. When team members stay, we can:

- **Deepen your expertise** — Advance from foundational skills to specialized leadership roles
- **Reduce your commute stress** — Build stability without relocating every few years
- **Preserve team continuity** — Maintain the relationships and protocols that make our practice exceptional
- **Ensure your career growth** — Invest in your professional development knowing you'll be here to apply it

This mutual commitment creates the stable, collaborative environment that sets us apart.
:::

### Our Values and Innovation {.unnumbered}

We are committed to:

- Patient-centered care excellence
- Continuous professional development
- Collaborative team environment
- Supportive work culture
- Quality pediatric dental services

::: {.callout-tip}
## Our Distinguished Practice Philosophy

### Excellence in Ethical Decision-Making
Our reputation for exceptional care stems from our unwavering commitment to this proven hierarchy:

1. **Child's Best Interest First**  

   - Uncompromising commitment to evidence-based care
   - Treatment plans based solely on dental needs
   - Long-term oral health outcomes as primary driver

2. **Parental Understanding & Collaboration**  

   - Clear communication of treatment rationales
   - Education about alternative approaches
   - Building trust through transparency

3. **Public Perception & Reviews**  

   - Never compromise care quality for ratings
   - Authentic patient experiences over curated content
   - Earn reputation through clinical excellence

### Our Professional Excellence Standards
Our selective approach ensures optimal outcomes by:

- Maintaining clinical integrity above external pressures
- Prioritizing authentic patient care over social considerations
- Ensuring harmony between all care priorities

*Join professionals who confidently communicate these evidence-based principles and uphold clinical excellence in every decision.*
:::

::: {.callout-important}
## Our Unique Approach: Visual Knowledge Sharing

What sets us apart is our commitment to visual documentation and knowledge sharing. As part of our team, you'll contribute to innovative initiatives that preserve and share best practices across our practice.
:::

### Video Documentation Initiative

- Capture essential clinical procedures and workflows
- Document nuanced interactions and best practices
- Record demonstrations of proper techniques and protocols
- Preserve expert knowledge through visual medium

### Knowledge Preservation Goals

- Create a visual library of standardized procedures
- Document subtle aspects of patient care that are difficult to convey in text
- Capture the choreography of team coordination
- Preserve experienced staff's intuitive knowledge

### Technical Requirements

- Basic video recording using mobile devices
- Simple video editing skills
- Organization of content for internal training
- Ability to maintain professional standards in documentation

This innovative approach helps us:

- Standardize our high-quality care delivery
- Enhance team training and coordination
- Preserve and share best practices
- Maintain consistent service excellence

*Our commitment to visual documentation sets us apart in pediatric dental care, ensuring our high standards are maintained and shared effectively.*

::: {.callout-important}
## Before Proceeding
Please review the above information carefully. Understanding our practice philosophy, values, and unique approach to knowledge sharing is essential for all team members. You will be expected to actively participate in and contribute to these initiatives.
:::

